.TH pipes.sh 6 "21 Jul 2026" "2.0.0" "pipes.sh Python rewrite"
.SH NAME
pipes.sh \- animated pipes terminal screensaver
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B pipes.sh
[\fIOPTION\fR]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B pipes.sh
is an unofficial, independently maintained Python rewrite of the classic
pipes.sh terminal screensaver. It requires Python 3.10 or newer and uses
POSIX terminal APIs plus terminfo directly; it does not execute tput, stty,
or a shell at runtime.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B -p [1-]
Number of independent pipes. Default: 1.
.TP
.B -t [0-9]
Select a built-in pipe type. Repeatable. Default: 0.
.TP
.B -t c[16 chars]
Add a custom type containing exactly 16 printable, single-cell Unicode
codepoints in old-direction by new-direction order.
.TP
.B -c [INDEX]
Add a decimal terminfo foreground-color index. Repeatable.
.TP
.B -c #[HEX]
Add a hexadecimal terminfo foreground-color index. Repeatable.
.TP
.B -f [20-100]
Frame rate. Default: 75.
.TP
.B -s [5-15]
Straight-probability denominator. Default: 13. Interactive control can reduce
this to 3 for historical compatibility.
.TP
.B -r [0-]
Clear after this many drawn pipe characters. Zero disables automatic clearing.
Default: 2000.
.TP
.B -R
Randomize starting positions and directions.
.TP
.B -B
Disable bold at startup.
.TP
.B -C
Disable color at startup.
.TP
.B -K
Keep pipe colors and types when crossing screen edges.
.TP
.B -h, --help
Display help and exit without requiring a TTY.
.TP
.B -v, --version
Display version and exit without requiring a TTY.
.TP
.B --self-test
Run deterministic, non-interactive integrity checks. This also works with
python -O.
.TP
.B --seed INTEGER
Use a deterministic random seed.
.SH PIPE TYPES
The ten built-in types are heavy box drawing, light arc, light square, double
box drawing, ASCII plus, ASCII slash, dots, dot/O, railway, and knobby.
Each contains 16 transition characters indexed as old_direction * 4 +
new_direction. Directions are up, right, down, and left; 180-degree turns are
never generated.
.SH COLORS
Color indices are encoded with the terminal's setaf capability. Terminals may
advertise 8, 16, 256, or direct-color index spaces. If no color capability is
available, pipes.sh continues without color. Out-of-range indices are rejected
before terminal attributes are changed.
.SH KEYBOARD CONTROLS
Press any key to quit except:
.TP
.B P / O
Increase/decrease straight probability denominator.
.TP
.B F / D
Increase/decrease frame rate.
.TP
.B B
Toggle bold immediately.
.TP
.B C
Toggle color immediately.
.TP
.B K
Toggle keeping type and color across edges.
.SH TERMINAL SAFETY
Interactive mode requires TTY stdin and stdout, a non-empty TERM other than
dumb, and working terminfo. Original terminal attributes, cursor visibility,
alternate-screen state, SGR state, and signal handlers are restored through an
idempotent cleanup path.
.SH HISTORY
pipes.sh was originally created by Matthew Simpson in 2010, later developed by
Yu-Jie Lin, and maintained by the Pipeseroni/pipes.sh contributors. The MIT
license was added in 2015. Version 2.0.0 is an independent Python rewrite
maintained by xnixjoyer and is not an official Pipeseroni release.
